article.headline: Mississippi 74, Arkansas 65
article.story: OXFORD, Miss. -- Terrico White scored 18 points as Mississippi placed four players in double figures on Wednesday night to defeat Arkansas 74-65. David Huertas added 16 points, while Zach Graham had 12 points and Murphy Holloway chipped in 11 for the Rebels (10-5, 1-1 Southeastern Conference). Courtney Fortson scored 24 points and Terrance Henry had 19 to lead Arkansas (12-3, 0-2). Ole Miss led 34-24 at halftime after leading by as many as 21 points in the opening 15 minutes. Arkansas answered with a 17-2 run to get within 34-28 with 18:23 left. Fortson had eight points and an assist to highlight the surge. The Rebels regained control with a 17-4 run, highlighted by six points from Graham, for a 51-32 lead with 11:21 left. Ole Miss hit 16 of 18 free throws in the final 10 minutes to seal the win.
